<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf665035f-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3501"><num value="3501">§ 3501.</num><heading> Number of passengers</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6650360-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3501/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> Each certificate of inspection issued to a vessel carrying passengers (except a ferry) shall include a statement on the number of passengers that the vessel is permitted to carry.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6650361-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3501/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><chapeau> The owner, charterer, managing operator, agent, master, or individual in charge of a vessel is liable to a person suing them for carrying more passengers than the number of passengers permitted by the certificate of inspection in an amount equal to—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6650362-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3501/b/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> passage money; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6650363-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3501/b/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> $100 for each passenger in excess of the number of passengers permitted.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6650364-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3501/c"><num value="c">(c)</num><content> An owner, charterer, managing operator, agent, master, or individual in charge of a vessel that knowingly carries more passengers than the number of passengers permitted by the certificate of inspection also shall be fined not more than $100, imprisoned for not more than 30 days, or both.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6650365-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3501/d"><num value="d">(d)</num><content> The vessel also is liable in rem for a penalty under this section.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6650366-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s3501/e"><num value="e">(e)</num><content> An offshore supply vessel may not carry passengers except in an emergency.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf6650367-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/519">97 Stat. 519</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/99/36/s1/a/2">Pub. L. 99–36, § 1(a)(2)</ref>, <date date="1985-05-15">May 15, 1985</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/99/67">99 Stat. 67</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
